# Dynatrace Log Shipping — Cost‑Controlled Opt‑In Model for VMs & AKS

**Owner:** Platform Engineering  
**Last updated:** {{today}}  
**Status:** Implement **this sprint**; release **end of Sprint 4**

***

## 1) Executive Summary

We will implement a **cost‑controlled log ingestion model** in Dynatrace:

*   **Default**: only the **minimum platform logs** are ingested. Application logs are **not** ingested by default (cost control).
*   **Opt‑in**: App owners can **explicitly enable** their logs:
    *   **VMs**: by writing logs into a **defined directory** that we ingest.
    *   **AKS**: by **labeling/annotating** their namespaces/pods per convention and writing logs to **stdout/stderr** (preferred) or using a sidecar to forward file logs to stdout. Dynatrace’s Kubernetes log module automatically discovers container stdout/stderr and can be controlled centrally via cluster‑scoped **log ingest rules** that match Kubernetes metadata. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/ingest-from/setup-on-k8s/deployment/k8s-log-monitoring), [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-logs-from-kubernetes)

This approach leverages:

*   **Dynatrace OneAgent/Kubernetes Log module** auto‑discovery of container stdout/stderr, with **central “Log ingest rules”** to include/exclude sources. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/ingest-from/setup-on-k8s/deployment/k8s-log-monitoring), [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)
*   **Dynatrace custom log sources** for VMs when a directory must be whitelisted, combined with ingest rules to store only what we approve. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-custom-log-source)

***

## 2) Scope & goals

*   **In‑scope**: Linux & Windows VMs with OneAgent; AKS clusters with Dynatrace Operator.
*   **Out‑of‑scope**: Non‑Kubernetes container platforms; third‑party collectors running outside the agreed model.

**Goals**

1.  Default posture: **ingest only platform‑essential logs**. (Define “minimum set” with 2nd‑level Ops.)
2.  **Self‑service opt‑in** for application logs (VMs & AKS).
3.  **Documented conventions** and **verification steps**.
4.  **Inventory updates** in Dynatrace documentation.

***

## 3) Target design (high level)

### 3.1 VMs

*   **Convention** (proposal):
    *   Linux app logs: `/var/log/dynatrace/app-logs/`
    *   Windows app logs: `C:\Dynatrace\Logs\`
*   **Dynatrace**: create **Custom log source** pointing to these paths; then add **Log ingest rules** to include these paths and **exclude all other application log paths** by default. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-custom-log-source), [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)

### 3.2 AKS

*   Use **Dynatrace Operator**; enable **logMonitoring**. The log module automatically discovers container **stdout/stderr**; file logs inside containers are **not** discovered unless shipped to stdout (use app change or sidecar). [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/ingest-from/setup-on-k8s/deployment/k8s-log-monitoring), [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-logs-from-kubernetes)
*   **Opt‑in** via **namespace label** (e.g., `dt.logs=enabled`) and **cluster‑scoped ingest rule** that includes only those namespaces; default excludes everything except the minimum platform logs. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)
*   If you need to limit Dynatrace injection (for full‑stack) to a subset of namespaces, use `namespaceSelector` in the **DynaKube** CR (Operator) and add an allow‑label (e.g., `dt-monitoring=true`). [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/ingest-from/setup-on-k8s/guides/deployment-and-configuration/monitoring-and-instrumentation/annotate)

> **Note**: Kubernetes events can also be monitored and filtered in Dynatrace if needed. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/observe/infrastructure-observability/container-platform-monitoring/kubernetes-monitoring/monitor-events-kubernetes)

