## 5) Implementation — **VMs**

### 5.1 OneAgent checks (host level)

1.  Verify log monitoring status (optional; enabled by default):
    *   **Global**: *Settings → Monitoring → Monitored technologies → Log Monitoring* (ensure enabled). [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/log-monitoring/log-monitoring-configuration)
    *   **Host** CLI:
        ```bash
        # Linux
        ./oneagentctl --get-app-log-content-access
        # Windows (PowerShell)
        .\oneagentctl.exe --get-app-log-content-access
        ```
        Enable if needed:
        ```bash
        ./oneagentctl --set-app-log-content-access=true
        .\oneagentctl.exe --set-app-log-content-access=true
        ```
        (Restart OneAgent service after change.) [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/log-monitoring/log-monitoring-configuration)

### 5.2 Define **Custom log source** (central)

Dynatrace UI: **Settings → Log Monitoring → Custom log sources → Add custom log source**:

*   Rule name: `VM-App-Logs`
*   **Log path** (Linux): `/var/log/dynatrace/app-logs/*.log`
*   **Log path** (Windows): `C:\Dynatrace\Logs\*.log`
*   (Optional) bind to Process Groups if you need tighter scoping.
*   Save.  
    Custom sources let OneAgent monitor paths that aren’t auto‑detected. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-custom-log-source)

### 5.3 Create **Log ingest rules** (central)

Dynatrace UI: **Settings → Log Monitoring → Log ingest rules**:

1.  **Default “exclude”** (environment scope):
    *   Rule: `Exclude-All-App-Logs`
    *   Type: **Exclude from storage**
    *   Matchers: *broad patterns* that would otherwise pull app logs (e.g., `/var/log/**`, except the allowlist path).
    *   This acts as a guardrail. (Rules are processed top‑to‑bottom; host‑scope overrides environment‑scope.) [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)

2.  **Allowlist for our folder(s)** (environment or host group scope):
    *   Rule: `Include-VM-App-Log-Dir`
    *   Type: **Include in storage**
    *   Matcher: **Log source** `=/var/log/dynatrace/app-logs/*.log` (Linux) and `=C:\Dynatrace\Logs\*.log` (Windows).
    *   (Optional) Add **content matchers** (e.g., only `ERROR|WARN`) to further reduce costs. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)

> **Why this works:** OneAgent auto‑discovers many logs, but only **ingest rules** decide what is stored/billed. Use include/exclude rules to control costs at scale. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-use-cases/lma-oa-logs-ingest), [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)

### 5.4 VM test & verification

*   On a **test VM**, write a small file under the folder and ensure it appears in **Dynatrace → Logs**; files elsewhere should **not** appear.
*   Use the built‑in **Log ingestion overview** dashboard to verify volumes. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-use-cases/lma-oa-logs-ingest)

