Follow “Full‑Stack observability” or “Platform monitoring + Log module” quickstart. Example (Helm/OCI per docs): [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/ingest-from/setup-on-k8s/deployment/full-stack-observability)

```bash
# (Example) Install Dynatrace Operator using Helm (per official docs)
# See docs for the current commands and flags
```

### 6.2 Enable **logMonitoring** in DynaKube CR

Create or update the **DynaKube** custom resource and include `spec.logMonitoring: {}`. This enables the log module (either with OneAgent on node or standalone mode depending on your observability option). [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/ingest-from/setup-on-k8s/deployment/k8s-log-monitoring)

```yaml
apiVersion: dynatrace.com/v1beta5
kind: DynaKube
metadata:
  name: dynakube
  namespace: dynatrace
spec:
  apiUrl: https://<YOUR_ENV>.live.dynatrace.com/api
  # Full-stack example: oneAgent.cloudNativeFullStack: {}
  logMonitoring: {}
```

**What gets collected?**  
The module **auto‑discovers container stdout/stderr** files; log records are enriched with Kubernetes metadata (namespace, pod, container, etc.). It **does not** discover file logs inside the container filesystem; for those, **write to stdout** or use a **sidecar** that tails files to stdout. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-logs-from-kubernetes)

### 6.3 Namespace‑level **opt‑in** convention

We’ll only ingest logs from namespaces labeled `dt.logs=enabled`.

1.  App team labels their namespace:

```bash
kubectl label namespace my-app-ns dt.logs=enabled --overwrite
```

2.  Create **cluster‑scoped Log ingest rule(s)** in Dynatrace to **Include** logs **only** where `k8s.namespace.name` matches namespaces labeled `dt.logs=enabled` (or maintain an allowlist of those namespaces in the rule). Dynatrace supports controlling Kubernetes log ingestion with **Kubernetes metadata** matchers; rules can be scoped at **Kubernetes cluster level** for precise control. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-logs-from-kubernetes), [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)

> If you also want to limit **OneAgent injection** to certain namespaces (for full‑stack), configure the DynaKube **`namespaceSelector`** to include only namespaces with `dt-monitoring=true`. This controls injection, not ingestion, but often you’ll use both controls together. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/ingest-from/setup-on-k8s/guides/deployment-and-configuration/monitoring-and-instrumentation/annotate)

### 6.4 Pod‑level annotation (optional fine‑grain)

For temporary inclusion/exclusion at pod level, teams can add annotations and you can refine **ingest rules** with pod metadata. Dynatrace supports **metadata enrichment** via labels/annotations; the Operator also supports annotation/label‑based monitoring controls (see docs for available keys). [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/ingest-from/setup-on-k8s/guides/deployment-and-configuration/monitoring-and-instrumentation/annotate), [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-logs-from-kubernetes)

### 6.5 AKS test & verification

*   **Test namespace** without label → logs should **not** appear.
*   Label `dt.logs=enabled` → logs start appearing (stdout/stderr).
*   For file‑based logs, validate the **sidecar to stdout** pattern (e.g., `tail -F /app/log/*.log` to stdout). Dynatrace sees stdout; no file mounts needed at the agent. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-logs-from-kubernetes)

