## 7) Dynatrace — **Exact configuration examples**

### 7.1 **Log ingest rule** examples (UI)

**Path:** *Settings → Log Monitoring → Log ingest rules*

**A) Global default exclude (guardrail)**

*   **Name**: `Exclude-NonPlatform-Logs`
*   **Type**: **Exclude from storage**
*   **Scope**: Environment (or per cluster override)
*   **Matchers**: Broad app paths (refine as you learn).  
    Rules are processed **top‑to‑bottom**, and can be overridden at host/cluster scopes. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)

**B) VM allowlist directories**

*   **Name**: `Include-VM-App-Logs-Folders`
*   **Type**: **Include in storage**
*   **Matchers**: **Log source**
    *   `/var/log/dynatrace/app-logs/*.log`
    *   `C:\Dynatrace\Logs\*.log`
*   (Optional) Add content/level matchers (e.g., `ERROR|WARN`) to reduce volume. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)

**C) AKS namespace allowlist (opt‑in)**

*   **Name**: `Include-AKS-OptIn-Namespaces`
*   **Type**: **Include in storage**
*   **Scope**: **Kubernetes cluster** (override)
*   **Matchers**: `k8s.namespace.name IN [ "team-a", "payments", "foo-bar" ]`  
    (Use your allowlisted namespaces labeled `dt.logs=enabled`.) Dynatrace allows controlling ingestion with **Kubernetes metadata** and configuring rules at **Kubernetes cluster** scope. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-logs-from-kubernetes)

> Tip: Keep a small “starter allowlist” this sprint; expand later. The **Enablement Lab** walkthrough shows where to create rules and how cluster overrides work. [\[dynatrace-....github.io\]](https://dynatrace-wwse.github.io/enablement-dynatrace-log-ingest-101/5-configure-dynatrace/)

### 7.2 **Custom log source** (VMs)

**Path:** *Settings → Log Monitoring → Custom log sources → Add*

*   **Rule name**: `VM-App-Logs`
*   **Log path**: add the OS‑specific path(s)
*   (Optional) set encoding, allow binary content if needed.  
    This enables OneAgent to track those files; **ingest still requires a rule** (above). [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-custom-log-source)

### 7.3 **DynaKube CR** (Operator) — log module enabled + selective injection (optional)

```yaml
apiVersion: dynatrace.com/v1beta5
kind: DynaKube
metadata:
  name: dynakube
  namespace: dynatrace
spec:
  apiUrl: https://<YOUR_ENV>.live.dynatrace.com/api

  # Enable log module
  logMonitoring: {}

  # (Optional) Only inject into namespaces you label dt-monitoring=true
  oneAgent:
    cloudNativeFullStack:
      namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          dt-monitoring: "true"
```

*   `logMonitoring: {}` enables the log module (auto‑discovers stdout/stderr). [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/ingest-from/setup-on-k8s/deployment/k8s-log-monitoring)
*   `namespaceSelector` lets you limit full‑stack injection to labeled namespaces. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/ingest-from/setup-on-k8s/guides/deployment-and-configuration/monitoring-and-instrumentation/annotate)

