## 8) App team guidance (to include in Academy)

### 8.1 VMs (developers)

*   **To ship logs to Dynatrace**: write your log files to:
    *   Linux: `/var/log/dynatrace/app-logs/`
    *   Windows: `C:\Dynatrace\Logs\`
*   Don’t write secrets/PPI to logs; follow our **masking** policy.
*   Expect ingestion within \~1–2 minutes after first write (check Logs app).

### 8.2 AKS (developers)

*   **Preferred**: write logs to **stdout/stderr**. Dynatrace’s log module auto‑discovers container output. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-logs-from-kubernetes)
*   **If your app writes files**, add a **sidecar** to tail files to stdout; or refactor logging to stdout. Dynatrace’s module does not read container filesystem logs by itself. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-logs-from-kubernetes)
*   Ask your Platform contact to **label your namespace**:
    ```bash
    kubectl label ns <your-ns> dt.logs=enabled --overwrite
    ```
    Your logs appear after the cluster‑scoped rule includes your namespace.
*   Add consistent labels to your Pods (e.g., `app.kubernetes.io/name`, `team`, `env`) to improve mapping and search. Dynatrace **enriches logs with k8s metadata** automatically. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-logs-from-kubernetes)

