# Appendices — Copy/Paste **Configuration Examples**

## A) Dynatrace **Log ingest rule** (illustrative matcher JSON)

> Configure via **UI** under *Settings → Log Monitoring → Log ingest rules*. The following shows an **illustrative** Settings payload structure for documentation purposes. Use UI unless you manage settings via API.

```jsonc
// Include logs from AKS namespaces that opted in (example allowlist)
{
  "enabled": true,
  "send-to-storage": true,
  "matchers": [
    { "attribute": "k8s.namespace.name", "operator": "IN", "values": ["payments", "orders", "team-a"] }
  ],
  "name": "Include-AKS-OptIn-Namespaces"
}
```

Dynatrace supports controlling Kubernetes log ingestion with **Kubernetes metadata** and cluster‑level overrides for precise control. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-logs-from-kubernetes), [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)

```jsonc
// Include only VM app directories (Linux & Windows)
{
  "enabled": true,
  "send-to-storage": true,
  "matchers": [
    { "attribute": "log.source", "operator": "MATCHES", "values": ["/var/log/dynatrace/app-logs/*.log", "C:\\\\Dynatrace\\\\Logs\\\\*.log"] }
  ],
  "name": "Include-VM-App-Log-Dir"
}
```

Custom log sources define the paths; ingest rules decide what’s stored/billed. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-custom-log-source), [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)

```jsonc
// Default guardrail - exclude broad app paths (refine for your env)
{
  "enabled": true,
  "send-to-storage": false, // Exclude
  "matchers": [
    { "attribute": "log.source", "operator": "MATCHES", "values": ["/var/log/**","C:\\\\**"] }
  ],
  "name": "Exclude-NonPlatform-Logs"
}
```

Rules are processed top‑to‑bottom; host/cluster scopes can override environment scope. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)

