## E) Operational tips for **cost control**

*   Start with a **narrow allowlist**; expand only on request.
*   Prefer **stdout/stderr** for containers, avoid file logs in containers unless a sidecar tails to stdout. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-logs-from-kubernetes)
*   Use **content/level matchers** (e.g., `ERROR|WARN`) where useful. Dynatrace recommends central control of OneAgent ingestion with Settings 2.0 rules and advanced log settings at scale. [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/advanced-log-settings), [\[docs.dynatrace.com\]](https://docs.dynatrace.com/docs/analyze-explore-automate/logs/lma-log-ingestion/lma-log-ingestion-via-oa/lma-log-storage-configuration)

